    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix buffer overflow in AttachReject message decoding\n\n### Summary\nThe `decode_attach_reject` function in the EMM message handler could cause a buffer overread when processing malformed Attach Reject messages. The function accessed buffer data without proper length validation in the optional field decoding loop.\n\nThis issue occurred when the UE received an Attach Reject message with an incomplete optional field. The function would attempt to read beyond the end of the provided buffer, potentially causing a segmentation fault or memory corruption.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/EMM/MSG/AttachReject.c`: Added proper buffer length validation and error handling.\n- Improved consistency with other NAS message decoders by adding logging macros.\n- Fixed signed/unsigned comparison in the while loop condition to prevent integer underflow.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce this issue:\n1. Send an Attach Reject message with an incomplete ESM Message Container IE\n2. The UE will attempt to decode the message and access memory beyond the buffer bounds\n3. This results in either a segmentation fault or undefined behavior depending on memory layout\n\nThe fix ensures that all buffer accesses are properly bounds-checked before reading data, preventing the overflow condition.\n"
}